When Wolf learns that Josh has been turned over to Internal Stray Enforcement, he decides to appeal his imprisonment to the NAG's Supreme Overlord, Vise.

title: The Handmaid's Tale
desc: June and the rest of the Handmaids shun Ofmatthew, and both are pushed to their limit at the hands of Aunt Lydia. Aunt Lydia reflects on her life and relationships before the rise of Gilead.

title: FEMEN: Sextremism in Canada
desc: Their objective is to destroy patriarchy; their weapons are bare breasts. FEMEN 'sextremists' have now set up shop in more than 10 countries, but only have one active branch in North America.

title: The Motorcycle Diaries
desc: A highly inspiring adventure based on the journals of Ernesto 'Che' Guevara as he journeys by motorcycle through South America with his best friend.

title: The Darjeeling Limited
desc: A year after their father's death, three American brothers, Francis, Peter and Jack - who haven't spoken since the funeral - embark on a soul-searching journey across India on board the titular train. The brothers, who don't get along very well, use the time to get to know each other better and begin to ponder questions like why they don't like each other, and why their mother didn't attend the funeral. Francis, whose face is completely bandaged due to a recent motorcycle accident, reveals that their mother has entered a convent in India, and the real reason for organising the trip was to find her.

title: Results
desc: Recently divorced, newly rich, and utterly miserable, Danny is proof that money can't buy happiness. Danny's well-funded misery is interrupted by a momentous trip to the local gym, where he meets self-styled guru and owner Trevor and irresistibly acerbic trainer Kat. Soon, their three lives are inextricably knotted, both professionally and personally.

title: Novitiate
desc: Spanning over a decade, from the early 1950s through to the mid-60s, this film is about a young girl's first experience with love. In this case, her first love is God. Raised by a vehemently non-religious, single mother in rural Tennessee, a scholarship to Catholic school soon finds Cathleen drawn into all the mystery and romanticism of a life devoted to the worship and servitude of God. With the dawn of the Vatican II era, radical changes in the Church are threatening the course of nuns' lives. Cathleen finds herself struggling with issues of faith, sexuality, and the changing administration. As she progresses from the postulant to the novitiate stage of training, she finds her faith repeatedly confronted and challenged by the harsh, often inhumane realities of being a servant of God.

title: Chalet Girl
desc: Pretty tomboy Kim used to be a champion skateboarder, but now she flips burgers to support herself and her dad. Opportunity comes knocking when she flukes a winter-long catering job in one of the plushest ski chalets in the Alps. At first, Kim is baffled by this bizarre new world of posh people, vintage champagne, epic mountains and waist-deep powder. Then Kim discovers snowboarding, and her natural talent soon sees her training for the end-of-season competition, with a chance to win major prize money. But before she can become a champion again, Kim needs to overcome her deepest fears - and figure out what's going on with Jonny, her boss' handsome but apparently unavailable son.

title: Whisky Galore!
desc: During World War II, the tiny Scottish island of Todday runs out of whisky. When the freighter SS Cabinet Minister runs aground nearby during a heavy fog, the islanders are delighted to learn that its cargo consists of 50,000 cases of whisky. When officious English commanding officer Captain Waggett demands return of the liquor, shopkeeper Joseph Macroon and his daughters, Peggy and Catriona, spearhead an island rebellion.

title: The Cup
desc: Young students at a Tibetan monastery try to raise money to rent a satellite dish to watch the 1998 France versus Brazil soccer final.

title: CJ7
desc: A poor father and his young son's lives are turned upside down when a fascinating and strange new pet enters their world. Amid the resulting comic mayhem, they ultimately learn a poignant lesson about the true nature of family and the things money can't buy.

title: The Life and Death of Colonel Blimp
desc: An artistic masterpiece detailing the experiences of a British officer, Clive Candy, through the trials and tribulations of his army career. During the Boer War, Candy is sent to Berlin to trap a spy. There he befriends a German officer, Theo, who marries the girl Candy is in love with. During WWI, Candy marries a girl who resembles her and helps Theo, now a POW, get repatriated. He comes back in WWII as a Brigadier General, and once again encounters Theo. He is captured, however, and the two are forced to either aid or betray each other.

title: Roald Dahl's Esio Trot
desc: Retired bachelor Mr Hoppy is hopelessly in love with his neighbour Mrs Silver, but she is only interested in her pet tortoise Alfie, until Mr Hoppy hatches an audacious plan to win her love.

title: Mary and Max
desc: A tale of friendship between two unlikely pen pals: Mary, a lonely, eight-year-old girl living in the suburbs of Melbourne, and Max, a 44-year old, severely obese man living in New York.

title: Black Sea
desc: In order to make good with his former employers, a submarine captain takes a job with a shadowy backer to search the depths of the Black Sea for a submarine rumoured to be loaded with gold.

title: The Odyssey
desc: 1948. Jacques Cousteau, his wife and his two sons are living in paradise, in a beautiful house overlooking the Mediterranean. But all Cousteau can think of is adventure. Thanks to his invention, an independent aqualung allowing divers to breathe under water, he has discovered a whole new world. Now all he wants to do is explore this world. And he is willing to sacrifice everything to achieve this.

title: The Cook and the Chef
desc: When it comes to fine cheeses, we're spoilt for choice in Australia; there are over 100 different varieties being produced by Cheese Wright's all around the country.

title: Kitchen Hero
desc: In the early 1960s, more people in Ireland were employed in domestic service (cooks, gardeners, maids) than there were teachers. Donal meets Patricia Quinn Murphy who started her working life as an assistant cook aged 16, in a large house in Wexford, and learns about a recent but largely forgotten part of our social history. At Muckross Traditional Farms, Donal is shown how to make soda bread in a bastible and makes Gur cake, a popular Dublin sweet bread.

title: Nigella Kitchen
desc: Nigella Lawson conjures up more dazzling dishes from the heart of the home, finding inspiration anywhere and everywhere with delicious results. Recipes include the fabulously kitsch grasshopper pie - the brainchild of a night sat in front of the telly, and an easy, elegant, spatchcocked poussin with baby leaf salad and sourdough croutons - a treat for two from travels in San Francisco.

title: BBQ Crawl
desc: Danielle starts her barbecue road trip in Texas, the land of beef. She's visiting two joints owned by members of the Mueller family. The first owned by John Mueller, the rebellious grandson of Texas barbecue legend Louie Mueller.

title: BBQ Crawl
desc: Danielle visits the oldest barbecue joint in the state of Texas, the Southside Market. Their sausages are famous all over the world. She gets to eat them and see how they're made.

title: Sicily with Aldo and Enzo
desc: Monreale sits high up in the mountains overlooking Palermo and, being sufficiently far enough from the sea, it depends on its meat trade. The pretty and bustling town boasts a thriving collection of well-stocked butchers, one of which provides Aldo and Enzo with the lamb cutlets needed for their dish of Sicilian-style lamb. But, before they set up kitchen in the town square, Enzo and Aldo each have a very close shave.

title: Gourmet Farmer
desc: Matthew continues his exploration of the possibilities of preserving pork by heading off to meet some French providores - experts at preserving high end product in cans. Matthew returns enthusiastic with his findings, only to discover Australian health laws make such a venture prohibitively expensive and uncertain. Luckily he's found a butcher with a cool room where he can create sausages to test out at his stall.

title: Short Cuts to Glory: Matt Okine vs Food
desc: What's not to love about the traditional family dinner? Matt hangs out with Nathan Sasi and a roast chicken, Jill Dupleix's mashed potatoes are pure magic, and Bernard Chu's berry crumble is a guaranteed winner. Sarah Glover helps separate essential kitchen tools from the fluff, while Alice Zaslavsky talks about the pointy end of handling a knife.

title: Food Safari Italy
desc: Guy hunts rabbit with chef Daniel Airo-Farula, while Maeve visits Stefano Manfredi on the Central Coast where he has planted a vegetable garden full of Italian produce ready for a classic minestrone. In Melbourne, Adelina Pulford shows Guy how to make the silkiest creamy panna cotta with prosecco, while Italian expatriate Aldo Cozzi and his coffee roaster Geroge Sabados explain the rules of enjoying good Italian coffee.

title: Come Dine with Me
desc: Every week, five strangers take it in turns to throw a dinner party. But this is no ordinary supper, as the guests are secretly scoring the host, and at the end of the week the top-scoring host wins 1000 pounds.

title: Come Dine with Me
desc: Every week, five strangers take it in turns to throw a dinner party. But this is no ordinary supper, as the guests are secretly scoring the host, and at the end of the week the top-scoring host wins 1000 pounds.

title: Surfing the Menu
desc: Cockburn Sound is 20 minutes south of the Port of Fremantle in Western Australia. It's a natural sweeping bay sheltered by Garden Island which is a nature reserve and naval base. It's a remarkable area where industry and nature co-exist side-by-side. The boys cook a meal aboard a submarine for the local defence force and check out what life on board a sub is really like. Later that day, they go crabbing with brothers Brad and Mark Martin for the Sound's succulent blue swimmer crabs. Geoff Peck takes them out to his mussel lease where he explains how the mussels spawn, sow and grow themselves.

title: Oliver's Twist
desc: Jamie Oliver rustles up more tasty meals. Here, he joins a friend on a river boat in Windsor, where they prepare a lobster club sandwich and a dessert called Eton mess.

title: The Chefs' Line
desc: Sous chef Gianni from Mexican restaurant el Publico goes up against two home cooks. Can the passion of a home cook beat the professional skills of a chef?

title: Kriol Kitchen
desc: Patty Mamid shows us how to prepare creamy chilli squid and soybean seafood soup. Drawing on her multicultural heritage, Patty cooks up two exotic dishes of her own making.

title: Destination Flavour Down Under
desc: Adam explores New Zealand's North Island starting in the majestic kauri forests in the north. He visits Dargaville, the kumara capital of New Zealand, and then a kiwifruit farm in Te Puke. At Rotorua he is invited to a traditional Maori 'Hangi' and then joins an impromptu game of rugby. After visiting a farm running shorthorn cattle, Adam heads to the coast to experience another New Zealand tradition, the 'bach', a modest holiday shack. A dish of roast Shorthorn beef with kawakawa on the deck overlooking the ocean is a perfect end to his North Island trip.

title: Carnival Eats
desc: Host Noah Cappe lands in the LA County Fair for some sunny west coast eats like the jackfruit torta, a sumptuous Mexican sandwich using jackfruit instead of meat. Chicken Charlie's team fries up two crazy carnival innovations - the 'PB meatballs', classic meatballs in a peanut butter batter, and the 'cherry punch hot wings', traditional chicken wings with a cherry candy coating. Finally, Noah takes a tasty stroll through the rainbow ice cream garden, a treat as beautiful as it is tasty. Later, Noah heads to the Markham Fair in Ontario for the colourful and delicious pulled pork rainbow melt. He'll also taste a frosted fried turkey leg, coated in sugary cereal, and for dessert, the 'crispy cruncher'.

title: River Cottage Australia
desc: It's been nearly four months since Hugh returned to River Cottage in the UK to let Paul do it alone, but now he's back, and he's amazed at what he finds. Where there used to be run-down enclosures and sheds, there are now homes for chickens, ducks, pigs and a dairy cow. The vegetable beds they laid out together are now a mass of leafy winter greens, and the citrus grove is thriving. They decide to harvest what they can as starting point for a huge community cook-up they've got planned, but they'll need more food to feed the hungry throng. At the beach, Paul instructs Hugh in the fine art of beach-worm catching. Will they be able to catch the bait, let alone enough fish for a feed?

title: Surfing the Menu
desc: Esperance, on the south coast of Western Australia, is home to some of Australia's best beaches. It's pure, crystal clear waters flow straight from the Antarctic and creates the ideal breeding grounds for seafood, nature and surfers. The boys surf with Ben Curtis and Kev MacNeall, who's not only a fisherman and surfer but a beekeeper with hives in the forest. After a fishing trip on a shark boat, the boys cook on the balcony of the Esperance Surf Club, alongside one of the best views in Australia.

title: Oliver's Twist
desc: Jamie makes Spanish-style tapas dishes for a neighbour who plays in a ladies' football team.

title: The Chefs' Line
desc: Head chef Tommy from Mexican restaurant el Publico goes up against this best home cook. It's the ultimate David versus Goliath battle. Can the passion of a home cook beat a professional chef?

title: Kriol Kitchen
desc: Neville Poelina will show us how to make two delicious dishes with duck and bush turkey - making the most out of his outdoor 44 gallon homemade bush oven.

title: Destination Flavour Down Under
desc: Adam takes a short ferry ride across the Cook Straight to New Zealand's South Island, headed for Akaroa, a historic French settlement nestled in the heart of an ancient volcano. An interest in the famous greenshell mussels leads him to Havelock, home to an industry worth more than $300 million per year. Later he heads down to the coastal town of Kaikoura, the Maori word for 'a meal of crayfish'. At Akaroa, Adam takes inspiration from the town's French roots and puts a modern spin on the classic, lobster Thermidor.

title: Carnival Eats
desc: Noah Cappe heads to Vancouver to sample some amazing eats, like the truly Canadian poutine-stuffed burger, the shrimp fried rice balls and jerk chicken dumplings, which perfectly fuse fair food with cultural favourites, and the 'Donuccino', a meal and a milkshake all in one. Later, Noah seeks out the main attractions at the Fryeburg Fair in Maine where he finds heaven with the Pig Pile in Paradise, and eats local favourites like the lobster roll and Maine blueberry crepes.

title: The Cook and the Chef
desc: On a recent trip to the Tweed Valley, Maggie was really taken with how all the banana plantations were scattered high across the mountain slopes. Third generation grower, Andrew Everest, explains to Maggie that sub-tropical bananas have to be grown up high to protect them from frost.

title: The Cook and the Chef
desc: Simon is deep in discussion with the hotel's maitre d', Atef. Simon and Atef are looking at some changes in the menu and deciding on a corresponding change in the recommended wine match.

title: Donal's Cook, Eat, Burn
desc: Donal tackles Carrauntoohil, the highest mountain in Ireland. To help him reach the top, he cooks recipes specially designed to sustain energy on a challenging day of mountaineering. The featured recipes include gluten free pancakes, chilli with charred corn salsa, and roast squash salad. He also prepares a healthy snack of oat flapjacks to stop and eat while admiring the stunning Kerry scenery.

title: River Cottage Australia
desc: Time has passed and the seasons have changed at River Cottage Australia. Paul West is about to experience his first summer on the land. Will he have enough water, food and produce to keep the farm thriving throughout the dryer months?

title: Nigella Kitchen
desc: Truly heavenly meals don't have to start life with painfully expensive ingredients. Nigella's got a whole host of sublime recipes up her sleeve that hail from far more modest beginnings. Like South Indian vegetable curry, made from the wilting contents of a Monday morning fridge raid, decadent chocolate chip bread pudding, aka stale bread reincarnated Nigella-style. Beer braised pork knuckles with caraway, garlic, apples and potatoes - totally divine and cheap to boot.

title: Jimmy's Australian Food Adventure
desc: In Litchfield National Park, south-west of Darwin, Jimmy joins crocodile ranger Matt Wright for a close encounter with a giant saltwater crocodile. Chief scientist Charlie Manolis at Crocodylus Park Farm in Darwin describes the challenges of farming an apex predator. Jimmy's journey ends at Mindil Beach Market in Darwin, where he feels croc-in-the-wok could catch on.

title: The Great Australian Cookbook
desc: King of Spanish cuisine, and creator of iconic restaurant chain Movida, Frank Camorra heads home to where his love of food began: his mum's kitchen. Together they share some of their secrets of traditional Spanish dishes including tortilla de patatas and asadillo. Fusing local produce with native foods, all sourced on Country in his beloved Gumbaynggirr lands, Indigenous chef Clayton Donovan cooks up two of his young family's favourite meals: kangaroo san choy bow, and oysters with finger lime, carrot foam and avocado cream.

title: Jimmy Shu's Taste of the Territory
desc: Jimmy tastes some of Darwin's most popular street food from the stalls of the Parap Saturday market. Jimmy talks about Darwin's laksa obsession, and visits Mary's Laksa - a stall who have been serving laska for over 20 yeas.

title: Poh and Co.
desc: Poh and Jono start building a wood-fired pizza oven to enhance their outdoor entertaining area, so of course Poh enlists Andre's help to find a good tutor in the art of pizza dough. Both end up getting a lesson from Mauro Gulli, an immigrant from Calabria who does Andre's commercial baking and used to be a pizzaiolo in Italy. It's a lot of fun. Later, Poh and Jono, and Rhino and Tim, escape the chaos at home with a picnic at the gorgeous beach at Port Willunga, south of Adelaide.

title: Bullets
desc: In Brussels, a woman called Madina Taburova arrives in a container ship from Syria. Meanwhile, in a Helsinki ferry terminal, Jari Holma, a convicted drug felon, arrives from Stockholm. He is greeted by his girlfriend Almaz. Two female undercover police officers stake out the meeting. Unbeknown to them, officers from the Helsinki Drug Squad are also at the scene. When Almaz hands Holma a package of drugs, he gets paranoid and runs. The female undercover cops chase Holma, who shoots one of them dead and escapes.

title: Bullets

Karla Grant travels to the city of Montgomery in the United States' southern state of Alabama to speak with American lawyer and social justice campaigner Bryan Stevenson. In this in-depth discussion, Karla asks what needs to be done to lower these statistics and hears how Bryan is saving men from the electric chair.

title: Great British Railway Journeys
desc: Guided by his Victorian Bradshaw's Michael Portillo continues his journey north along Robert Stephenson's London to Birmingham line. He begins in Leicester, where he picks up the trail of the famous crook-backed King Richard III, who, Bradshaw's informs him, was buried at the Grey Priory. Michael finds out about the hunt for the king's remains and how scientists managed to prove it was him. From Rothley, Michael works his passage on the Great Central Railway to Loughborough, where the bells have been tolling since 1839.

title: Motorway
desc: Sean, an overconfident rookie with a need for speed, works for a covert police unit consisting of the best drivers in the force who tackle underworld racing and fugitives on the run. Jensen is one such target, a legendary escape driver for criminals, who has never been caught. As the body count and wrecked cars begin to pile, Sean turns to veteran cop Lo who almost lost his life years ago while chasing Jensen. Together they work to bring him down and the diamond heist being planned.

desc: Movie review program hosted by Margaret Pomeranz and David Stratton. They review The Edge and U Turn. They also interview director Oliver Stone. Includes a look at the Berlin Film Festival.

title: MythBusters
desc: The team plumb the depths and hit the heights with a double diving extravaganza. Adam and Jamie test a well-worn action movie cliche: that after a rooftop chase, the hero can make his escape by jumping into a conveniently placed dumpster on the street below. Meanwhile, Kari, Grant, and Tory probe a gruesome diving disaster: that a deep-sea diver in an old-style suit can be crushed into his helmet if the line connecting him to his surface air compressor breaks.

desc: The evil Shogun Takeshi has kidnapped Princess Woonsen and imprisoned her in his castle. Contestants aim to storm Takeshi's castle and free her.

title: The Orville
desc: When Issac shuts down, the crew head to his home planet to fix him, and uncover a shocking secret that was better off hidden.

title: 8 Out of 10 Cats Does Countdown
desc: It's Letters and Numbers with a whole bunch of comedians. Hosted by Jimmy Carr, Rachel Riley, and Susie Dent. Featuring guests Ivan Brackenbury, Alan Carr, Katherine Ryan, and Jason Manford.

title: Party of Five
desc: Emilio reunites with his band for a fundraiser that Lucia is hosting at the restaurant. Beto looks to win over Ella's dad, while Valentina hides her past from her dance class.

title: Live PD: Police Patrol
desc: The team investigates a fugitive foot chase in Florida, a resisting arrest case in OK, and a giant pot bust in Utah.

title: Live PD: Police Patrol
desc: The squad deals with a DUI senior citizen in Florida, an assault with a pick-up truck in Florida, and a violent ex-girlfriend in South Carolina.

title: My Extreme Life
desc: We meet Nikita, a 23-year-old who spends hours each day tapping items in her home convinced by her OCD that these rituals will protect her loved ones from harm.

title: The Feed
desc: Two-year-old Saxon desperately needs a bone marrow transplant to treat a rare autoimmune disease, but the recent restrictions on elective surgeries due to COVID-19 have left him and his parents in a dangerous limbo. Despite some operations resuming, Saxon - and many Australians like him - are yet to be given any information on when to expect their desperately needed procedures. Plus, the men dedicating their lives to prove that the Tasmanian tiger is still alive.

title: Game of Bros
desc: Wairangi Koopu will test the agility and coordination of our warriors in Poi Rakau. They will need to show their strength and endurance in a fruit carrying race, a favourite at the Heiva festival.

title: Novitiate
desc: Spanning over a decade, from the early 1950s through to the mid-60s, this film is about a young girl's first experience with love. In this case, her first love is God. Raised by a vehemently non-religious, single mother in rural Tennessee, a scholarship to Catholic school soon finds Cathleen drawn into all the mystery and romanticism of a life devoted to the worship and servitude of God. With the dawn of the Vatican II era, radical changes in the Church are threatening the course of nuns' lives. Cathleen finds herself struggling with issues of faith, sexuality, and the changing administration. As she progresses from the postulant to the novitiate stage of training, she finds her faith repeatedly confronted and challenged by the harsh, often inhumane realities of being a servant of God.

title: The Motorcycle Diaries
desc: A highly inspiring adventure based on the journals of Ernesto 'Che' Guevara as he journeys by motorcycle through South America with his best friend.

title: The Cup
desc: Young students at a Tibetan monastery try to raise money to rent a satellite dish to watch the 1998 France versus Brazil soccer final.

title: Mary and Max
desc: A tale of friendship between two unlikely pen pals: Mary, a lonely, eight-year-old girl living in the suburbs of Melbourne, and Max, a 44-year old, severely obese man living in New York.

title: The Odyssey
desc: 1948. Jacques Cousteau, his wife and his two sons are living in paradise, in a beautiful house overlooking the Mediterranean. But all Cousteau can think of is adventure. Thanks to his invention, an independent aqualung allowing divers to breathe under water, he has discovered a whole new world. Now all he wants to do is explore this world. And he is willing to sacrifice everything to achieve this.

title: The Secret of Moonacre
desc: This is an enchanting tale of magic and adventure. It follows the quest of 13-year-old orphan Maria Merryweather, who is sent away to live with her uncle, Sir Benjamin, in the mysterious Moonacre Manor. It is there that Maria uncovers the dark truth of the ancient curse that has nourished the feud that has been destroying Moonacre Valley for centuries. She has only until the next full moon to undo the curse and save Moonacre from destruction.

title: City of Ember
desc: An underground city is supposed to give shelter for 200 years. Unfortunately, power supply is failing, slowly but surely.

title: Whisky Galore!
desc: During World War II, the tiny Scottish island of Todday runs out of whisky. When the freighter SS Cabinet Minister runs aground nearby during a heavy fog, the islanders are delighted to learn that its cargo consists of 50,000 cases of whisky. When officious English commanding officer Captain Waggett demands return of the liquor, shopkeeper Joseph Macroon and his daughters, Peggy and Catriona, spearhead an island rebellion.

title: CJ7
desc: A poor father and his young son's lives are turned upside down when a fascinating and strange new pet enters their world. Amid the resulting comic mayhem, they ultimately learn a poignant lesson about the true nature of family and the things money can't buy.

title: Romeo and Juliet
desc: Romeo and Juliet secretly wed despite the sworn contempt their families hold for each other. It is not long, however, before a chain of fateful events changes the lives of both families forever.

title: Their Finest
desc: A British film crew attempt to boost morale during World War II by making a propaganda film after the Blitzkrieg.

title: The Grand Budapest Hotel
desc: Recounts the adventures of Gustave H, a legendary concierge at a famous European hotel between the wars, and Zero Moustafa, the lobby boy who becomes his most trusted friend.

title: Black Sea
desc: In order to make good with his former employers, a submarine captain takes a job with a shadowy backer to search the depths of the Black Sea for a submarine rumoured to be loaded with gold.

title: The Cook and the Chef
desc: Simon is deep in discussion with the hotel's maitre d', Atef. Simon and Atef are looking at some changes in the menu and deciding on a corresponding change in the recommended wine match.

title: Donal's Cook, Eat, Burn
desc: Donal tackles Carrauntoohil, the highest mountain in Ireland. To help him reach the top, he cooks recipes specially designed to sustain energy on a challenging day of mountaineering. The featured recipes include gluten free pancakes, chilli with charred corn salsa, and roast squash salad. He also prepares a healthy snack of oat flapjacks to stop and eat while admiring the stunning Kerry scenery.

title: Nigella Kitchen
desc: Truly heavenly meals don't have to start life with painfully expensive ingredients. Nigella's got a whole host of sublime recipes up her sleeve that hail from far more modest beginnings. Like South Indian vegetable curry, made from the wilting contents of a Monday morning fridge raid, decadent chocolate chip bread pudding, aka stale bread reincarnated Nigella-style. Beer braised pork knuckles with caraway, garlic, apples and potatoes - totally divine and cheap to boot.

title: BBQ Crawl
desc: Danielle cruises into Memphis, Tennessee, and although there are hundreds of prospective barbecue joints to visit, she only chooses one - AandR BBQ. It is the heart and soul of Memphis 'cue.

title: BBQ Crawl
desc: Danielle heads south to Mississippi to the crazy, fun-filled joint known as The Shed. Danielle is made an honoree Shed Hed as she hangs out, and chases alligators. Then, she joins the Shed family for Operation BBQ Rescue as they deliver barbecues to families in need who have been hit by the hurricane.

title: Jimmy's Australian Food Adventure
desc: In Litchfield National Park, south-west of Darwin, Jimmy joins crocodile ranger Matt Wright for a close encounter with a giant saltwater crocodile. Chief scientist Charlie Manolis at Crocodylus Park Farm in Darwin describes the challenges of farming an apex predator. Jimmy's journey ends at Mindil Beach Market in Darwin, where he feels croc-in-the-wok could catch on.

title: The Great Australian Cookbook
desc: King of Spanish cuisine, and creator of iconic restaurant chain Movida, Frank Camorra heads home to where his love of food began: his mum's kitchen. Together they share some of their secrets of traditional Spanish dishes including tortilla de patatas and asadillo. Fusing local produce with native foods, all sourced on Country in his beloved Gumbaynggirr lands, Indigenous chef Clayton Donovan cooks up two of his young family's favourite meals: kangaroo san choy bow, and oysters with finger lime, carrot foam and avocado cream.

title: Jimmy Shu's Taste of the Territory
desc: Jimmy tastes some of Darwin's most popular street food from the stalls of the Parap Saturday market. Jimmy talks about Darwin's laksa obsession, and visits Mary's Laksa - a stall who have been serving laska for over 20 yeas.

title: Poh and Co.
desc: Poh and Jono start building a wood-fired pizza oven to enhance their outdoor entertaining area, so of course Poh enlists Andre's help to find a good tutor in the art of pizza dough. Both end up getting a lesson from Mauro Gulli, an immigrant from Calabria who does Andre's commercial baking and used to be a pizzaiolo in Italy. It's a lot of fun. Later, Poh and Jono, and Rhino and Tim, escape the chaos at home with a picnic at the gorgeous beach at Port Willunga, south of Adelaide.

title: Come Dine with Me
desc: Every week, five strangers take it in turns to throw a dinner party. But this is no ordinary supper, as the guests are secretly scoring the host, and at the end of the week the top-scoring host wins 1000 pounds.

title: Surfing the Menu
desc: Esperance, on the south coast of Western Australia, is home to some of Australia's best beaches. It's pure, crystal clear waters flow straight from the Antarctic and creates the ideal breeding grounds for seafood, nature and surfers. The boys surf with Ben Curtis and Kev MacNeall, who's not only a fisherman and surfer but a beekeeper with hives in the forest. After a fishing trip on a shark boat, the boys cook on the balcony of the Esperance Surf Club, alongside one of the best views in Australia.

title: Oliver's Twist
desc: Jamie makes Spanish-style tapas dishes for a neighbour who plays in a ladies' football team.

title: The Chefs' Line
desc: Head chef Tommy from Mexican restaurant el Publico goes up against this best home cook. It's the ultimate David versus Goliath battle. Can the passion of a home cook beat a professional chef?

title: Kriol Kitchen
desc: Neville Poelina will show us how to make two delicious dishes with duck and bush turkey - making the most out of his outdoor 44 gallon homemade bush oven.

title: Destination Flavour Down Under
desc: Adam takes a short ferry ride across the Cook Straight to New Zealand's South Island, headed for Akaroa, a historic French settlement nestled in the heart of an ancient volcano. An interest in the famous greenshell mussels leads him to Havelock, home to an industry worth more than $300 million per year. Later he heads down to the coastal town of Kaikoura, the Maori word for 'a meal of crayfish'. At Akaroa, Adam takes inspiration from the town's French roots and puts a modern spin on the classic, lobster Thermidor.

title: Carnival Eats
desc: Noah Cappe heads to Vancouver to sample some amazing eats, like the truly Canadian poutine-stuffed burger, the shrimp fried rice balls and jerk chicken dumplings, which perfectly fuse fair food with cultural favourites, and the 'Donuccino', a meal and a milkshake all in one. Later, Noah seeks out the main attractions at the Fryeburg Fair in Maine where he finds heaven with the Pig Pile in Paradise, and eats local favourites like the lobster roll and Maine blueberry crepes.

title: River Cottage Australia
desc: Time has passed and the seasons have changed at River Cottage Australia. Paul West is about to experience his first summer on the land. Will he have enough water, food and produce to keep the farm thriving throughout the dryer months?

There's more to Mexican than tacos, including a dish that uses Australian green ants - the tuna tostada. Delight in carnitas de lechon (or suckling pig) and a super vanilla flan.

title: Kriol Kitchen
desc: Denise, Mitch and Ali turn the humble bush turkey into a delicious stew using basic vegetables and Asian sauces.

title: Destination Flavour Down Under
desc: Adam takes a scenic route to Gore and Invercargill on New Zealand's South Island, before heading to the stunning Lake Wakatipu. He spends a long day in the water fishing for trout with a former lawyer, meets a brewer who specialises in craft ciders and beers, and visits a local hunter for some fresh meats. Along the way he collects ingredients for a delicious New Zealand hunter's pie, the perfect dish to consume in front of a fire with snow-dusted mountains as the backdrop.

title: Carnival Eats
desc: Host Noah Cappe knows 'Dela-where' to find amazing fresh seafood, the Delaware State Fair in Harrington. Noah starts with the shrimp dog, succulent shrimp in a corn dog batter, and feels some soul with the Crabtastic Po' Boy, a whole, deep-fried soft shell crab in a sandwich. Noah will also sample a local Delaware classic with the apple scrapple burger before feeding his sweet tooth with the beer battered, deep-fried key lime pie.

title: The Cook and the Chef
desc: Maggie replicates beautiful lamb pies that she created for a charity event, while Simon gives shepherd's pie a vegetarian spin. Also on the menu is chocolate and lots of it, with a wicked chocolate ganache tart.

title: The Cook and the Chef
desc: South of Hobart in the delightfully named Sandfly, Simon found Gordon and Jane Brown growing an unusual crop: green tea. After getting over the shock of finding tea growing in Tassie, Simon found out that most black tea is actually grown in highland regions, so it's not actually all that unusual to grow tea in such a cold climate.

title: Donal's Cook, Eat, Burn
desc: Donal goes rock climbing on the beautiful but challenging North Antrim Coast. He prepares new recipes, specially selected to help the body recover after a day of activity and exertion, including seabass ceviche, beetroot burgers, pomegranate molasses chicken, and coconut macaroons.

title: River Cottage Australia
desc: Paul has learnt how to be a dairy farmer the hard way. It's time for Paul to make another tough lesson. How will he cope saying goodbye to another farm favourite?

title: Nigella Kitchen
desc: If you're home alone and deserve a treat, simple spaghetti is the answer. If you have people coming over and are pressed for time - Spanish chicken with chorizo and potatoes is the work of moments, with the leftovers turned into dreamy breakfast quesadillas. There's Nigella's no-fuss fruit tart and, for evenings when you need speed, ease, and restoration, there is lemony salmon with cherry tomato couscous. For those moments when cooking is beyond you, a chip kebab is the answer.

title: Paul Hollywood's Pies and Puds
desc: Paul Hollywood gets his best of British pies and puds well and truly spiced up with the irrepressible Levi Roots, before returning the favour with his own amazing Caribbean banana tarte tatin. With his recipes returning to home shores, he picks up an unusual use for seaweed, and creates choux puffs with home-grown mushrooms.

title: Rick Stein's German Bite
desc: Chef Rick Stein sets out on a German voyage with his usual appetite seeking out tantalising culinary gems. His journey is timed perfectly with the arrival of the new season's herring on the north German coast and the harvesting of white asparagus. He also heads inland towards Dusseldorf and the beautiful Rheingau region where he meets up with his son Jack and introduces him to the family legacy in that area as well as to some of the German Steins. This trip is particularly close to Rick's heart. Although he has always known he was of German descent, he knows very little of his German family.

Twelve days later, her badly beaten body was found dumped in a concrete culvert outside of town. Despite strong leads, the investigation failed to find her killer. Fifteen years on, Theresa's family are still desperately seeking answers. We retrace Theresa's last steps, find new leads and speak with authorities.

desc: Wembley befriends a rare mudbunny and gets an insight into life's greatest mystery.

title: Cocaine Trade Exposed: The Invisibles
desc: We follow investigative journalist Jeremy McDermott as he tracks down an Invisible who goes by the alias Memo Fantasma. Legend has it that in 1993, he stole a load of cocaine from Pablo Escobar and used that as his seed money to start his own hidden drug empire. He managed to get a free pass from US law enforcement by giving up his cohorts. He has morphed himself into a seemingly successful businessman with a construction empire, but where does the money come from?

title: The Missing

title: The Missing
desc: It's now 2015, and Julien's health is failing, but his determination to track down the missing girl means he's not finished with the Webster case just yet. Gemma is surprised by a phone call from Julien, and finds a new purpose that helps break through her stupor.

title: The Missing
desc: Secrets from the past are uncovered as Julien finally learns the truth behind Alice and Sophie's abduction. But time is running out, and nobody in Eckhausen will listen to him. However, they refuse to believe him and he falls under suspicion himself. With nowhere left to turn, how far will Julien go in his search to find the truth?

title: The Missing
desc: The truth of the events leading up to Alice's return to Eckhausen in 2014 are finally revealed. We see how she escaped her abductor, her reasons for coming back, and what led her to commit such a shocking act. But, as ever, the truth is far more complicated than anyone thought, and has far-reaching consequences that implicate multiple suspects on the Eckhausen base.

title: Running Wild with Bear Grylls
desc: Actor Don Cheadle joins Bear on a rigorous journey to the White Mountains of New England in this episode. Dropped from a helicopter into unyielding terrain, Don and Bear get creative with a deer antler to cross a raging river, rappel a massive shear cliff, and attempt a commando-worthy climb of a towering railroad bridge. But the discovery of a rotting porcupine carcass, which Bear eyes for dinner, will raise Don's pulse like nothing else. Along the way, Don details his family-oriented home life, the ups and down of a legendary career, and the secretive workings of a Marvel movie set.

title: Joe Wicks: The Body Coach

title: Gadget Man

title: Great British Food Revival

Giorgio is determined to find out why. Meanwhile, Jason Atherton goes into battle for the beleaguered British gooseberry. There used to be 2000 varieties, but today only four are produced commercially.

title: The Story of Europe
desc: For many Europeans, Europe is synonymous with the 'Christian Occident'. But like so much of what has shaped our civilisation, Christianity also comes from the East. It is not the only 'one-faith belief' that shapes the continent: even before Christianity, Judaism spread throughout the Roman Empire. On the Iberian Peninsula, Muslim Moors rule from the 8th to the 15th century. But that is not enough: the faith community of Christians is breaking up as well.

title: Adolf and Eva: Love and War

Revealing the truth behind the influential, ambitious and manipulative Nazi bride, this is the story of Eva's incredible rise - and dramatic fall.

title: Running Wild with Bear Grylls
desc: Actor Don Cheadle joins Bear on a rigorous journey to the White Mountains of New England in this episode. Dropped from a helicopter into unyielding terrain, Don and Bear get creative with a deer antler to cross a raging river, rappel a massive shear cliff, and attempt a commando-worthy climb of a towering railroad bridge. But the discovery of a rotting porcupine carcass, which Bear eyes for dinner, will raise Don's pulse like nothing else. Along the way, Don details his family-oriented home life, the ups and down of a legendary career, and the secretive workings of a Marvel movie set.

title: Joe Wicks: The Body Coach
desc: Joe Wicks, aka 'The Body Coach', is famed for his unique brand of exercise and nutrition. After taking the world of social media by storm and writing the second best-selling cookbook of all time, Lean in 15, Joe brings his popular fitness plans from the digital world to television screens, enrolling the public to join his fitness revolution.

title: Gadget Man
desc: Holidays are meant to be the most relaxing time of year, yet we often arrive back home more tired than when we left. How can gadgets take the stress out of the summer vacation?

title: Great British Food Revival
desc: Michelin-starred Giorgio Locatelli campaigns for the revival of the British sardine. Sardines thrive in the sea off Cornwall but, shockingly, people hardly eat any of them. Giorgio is determined to find out why. Meanwhile, Jason Atherton goes into battle for the beleaguered British gooseberry. There used to be 2000 varieties, but today only four are produced commercially.

title: The Story of Europe
desc: For many Europeans, Europe is synonymous with the 'Christian Occident'. But like so much of what has shaped our civilisation, Christianity also comes from the East. It is not the only 'one-faith belief' that shapes the continent: even before Christianity, Judaism spread throughout the Roman Empire. On the Iberian Peninsula, Muslim Moors rule from the 8th to the 15th century. But that is not enough: the faith community of Christians is breaking up as well.

title: Adolf and Eva: Love and War
desc: From teenage infatuation to her wedding to Hitler and suicide in the fuhrerbunker - this documentary reveals the shocking lengths to which Nazi Germany's secret First Lady went to rise to, and cling to, power. The Nazis kept Eva Braun's affair with Hitler hidden until the very end. But the Fuhrer's inner circle knew she had survived against the odds to become the most powerful woman in Germany. Revealing the truth behind the influential, ambitious and manipulative Nazi bride, this is the story of Eva's incredible rise - and dramatic fall.

title: Happy Endings
desc: Jane and Alex's sibling rivalry heats up, and Dave dates a new girl with a strange quirk.

title: Happy Endings
desc: Penny buys her first home, an 'amah-zing' condo complete with a wine fridge and Italian marble. But will the new digs really signal 'the year of Penny' and turn her life around?

title: Happy Endings
desc: Alex's store is a hit with teen girls, and Jane goes in search of her 'egg daughter'.

title: Happy Endings
desc: Penny's perpetually optimistic mother pays a visit.

title: Alone
desc: With winter almost upon them, the remaining participants come face-to-face with some of Patagonia's most dangerous and wily creatures. One survivalist struggles to catch a flighty prey, while another stalks Patagonia's largest and most elusive food source. A relentless adversary torments one participant, and another finds a deadly virus at their doorstep.

title: Stargate SG-1
desc: Captain Samantha Carter fights for equality and true love on a planet where the women are treated as property.

title: Ancient Aliens
desc: Deadly volcanic eruptions, cataclysmic earthquakes, and tsunamis capable of wiping out entire cities. Despite thousands of years of civilisation, man has yet to conquer Mother Nature. But are these disastrous events environmental phenomena? Or might there be some other, extraterrestrial force at work?

title: American Gods
desc: Trying to work things out with his dead and unfaithful wife, Shadow's emotional reunion is interrupted when he and Mr Wednesday are kidnapped by the New Gods.

title: American Gods
desc: On the run after the New Gods' show of force, Shadow and Mr Wednesday seek safe haven with one of Mr Wednesday's oldest friends, Vulcan, God of the Fire and the Forge.

title: Gangs of Central America
desc: In Central America, governments are struggling to deal with gang violence. We report on what's being done to rein in the gangs, and meet the victims who've become desperate to escape.

title: Black Sea
desc: In order to make good with his former employers, a submarine captain takes a job with a shadowy backer to search the depths of the Black Sea for a submarine rumoured to be loaded with gold.

title: The Secret of Moonacre
desc: This is an enchanting tale of magic and adventure. It follows the quest of 13-year-old orphan Maria Merryweather, who is sent away to live with her uncle, Sir Benjamin, in the mysterious Moonacre Manor. It is there that Maria uncovers the dark truth of the ancient curse that has nourished the feud that has been destroying Moonacre Valley for centuries. She has only until the next full moon to undo the curse and save Moonacre from destruction.

title: Their Finest
desc: A British film crew attempt to boost morale during World War II by making a propaganda film after the Blitzkrieg.

title: CJ7
desc: A poor father and his young son's lives are turned upside down when a fascinating and strange new pet enters their world. Amid the resulting comic mayhem, they ultimately learn a poignant lesson about the true nature of family and the things money can't buy.

title: Roald Dahl's Esio Trot
desc: Retired bachelor Mr Hoppy is hopelessly in love with his neighbour Mrs Silver, but she is only interested in her pet tortoise Alfie, until Mr Hoppy hatches an audacious plan to win her love.

title: The Life and Death of Colonel Blimp
desc: An artistic masterpiece detailing the experiences of a British officer, Clive Candy, through the trials and tribulations of his army career. During the Boer War, Candy is sent to Berlin to trap a spy. There he befriends a German officer, Theo, who marries the girl Candy is in love with. During WWI, Candy marries a girl who resembles her and helps Theo, now a POW, get repatriated. He comes back in WWII as a Brigadier General, and once again encounters Theo. He is captured, however, and the two are forced to either aid or betray each other.

title: Boychoir
desc: A troubled 11-year-old boy at a prestigious east coast music school clashes with the school's demanding choir master, in this inspiring drama the entire family can enjoy. The story of a talented youngster struggling against the odds to find his voice.

title: Our Little Sister
desc: Three sisters, Sachi, Yoshino and Chika, live together in a large house in the seaside city of Kamakura. When their father, absent from the family home for the last 15 years, dies, they travel to the countryside for his funeral and meet their shy 14-year-old half-sister, Suzu. Bonding quickly with the orphaned Suzu, they invite her to live with them. Suzu eagerly agrees, and a new life of joyful discovery begins for the four siblings.

title: City of Ember
desc: An underground city is supposed to give shelter for 200 years. Unfortunately, power supply is failing, slowly but surely.

title: The Odyssey
desc: 1948. Jacques Cousteau, his wife and his two sons are living in paradise, in a beautiful house overlooking the Mediterranean. But all Cousteau can think of is adventure. Thanks to his invention, an independent aqualung allowing divers to breathe under water, he has discovered a whole new world. Now all he wants to do is explore this world. And he is willing to sacrifice everything to achieve this.

title: 127 Hours
desc: This is the true story of mountain climber Aron Ralston's remarkable adventure to save himself after a fallen boulder crashes on his arm and traps him in an isolated canyon in Utah. Over the next five days, Ralston examines his life and survives the elements to finally discover he has the courage and the wherewithal to extricate himself by any means necessary, scale a 65ft wall and hike over 12km before he is finally rescued. Throughout his journey, Ralston recalls friends, lovers, family, as well as the last two people he ever had the chance to meet.

title: Loving Pablo
desc: The extraordinary story of the volatile love affair between Colombia's most famous journalist, Virginia Vallejo, and the world's most feared drug lord, Pablo Escobar. When Virginia first met Pablo, she was drawn to him by his charisma and contagious passion for his country and the people he loves. As their passionate affair intensified, so did the brutal violence and tyranny that surrounded Escobar's empire. As her world comes crashing down around her, Virginia must decide if she will support the man she loves or help bring down one of the most vicious criminals the world has ever known in this amazing story inspired by true events from Virginia's best-selling memoir.

title: The Cook and the Chef
desc: South of Hobart in the delightfully named Sandfly, Simon found Gordon and Jane Brown growing an unusual crop: green tea. After getting over the shock of finding tea growing in Tassie, Simon found out that most black tea is actually grown in highland regions, so it's not actually all that unusual to grow tea in such a cold climate.

title: Donal's Cook, Eat, Burn
desc: Donal goes rock climbing on the beautiful but challenging North Antrim Coast. He prepares new recipes, specially selected to help the body recover after a day of activity and exertion, including seabass ceviche, beetroot burgers, pomegranate molasses chicken, and coconut macaroons.

title: Nigella Kitchen
desc: If you're home alone and deserve a treat, simple spaghetti is the answer. If you have people coming over and are pressed for time - Spanish chicken with chorizo and potatoes is the work of moments, with the leftovers turned into dreamy breakfast quesadillas. There's Nigella's no-fuss fruit tart and, for evenings when you need speed, ease, and restoration, there is lemony salmon with cherry tomato couscous. For those moments when cooking is beyond you, a chip kebab is the answer.

title: BBQ Crawl
desc: Danielle is headed to the Decatur Jaycee's Riverfest to compete, but before she gets there, she's looking forward to meeting up with old friends and eating some local 'bama' cue.

title: BBQ Crawl
desc: Danielle heads east through Georgia, land of peaches and Bubba Q BBQ. Her buddy, William 'Bubba' Latimer, owns the place with his wife.

title: Paul Hollywood's Pies and Puds
desc: Paul Hollywood gets his best of British pies and puds well and truly spiced up with the irrepressible Levi Roots, before returning the favour with his own amazing Caribbean banana tarte tatin. With his recipes returning to home shores, he picks up an unusual use for seaweed, and creates choux puffs with home-grown mushrooms.

title: Rick Stein's German Bite
desc: Chef Rick Stein sets out on a German voyage with his usual appetite seeking out tantalising culinary gems. His journey is timed perfectly with the arrival of the new season's herring on the north German coast and the harvesting of white asparagus. He also heads inland towards Dusseldorf and the beautiful Rheingau region where he meets up with his son Jack and introduces him to the family legacy in that area as well as to some of the German Steins. This trip is particularly close to Rick's heart. Although he has always known he was of German descent, he knows very little of his German family.

title: Come Dine with Me
desc: Every week, five strangers take it in turns to throw a dinner party. But this is no ordinary supper, as the guests are secretly scoring the host, and at the end of the week the top-scoring host wins 1000 pounds.

title: Surfing the Menu: New Zealand
desc: Mark Gardner and Ben O'Donoghue take off on a Kiwi food surfari. Ben and Mark soar above the spectacular snow-covered Southern Alps in Gliders. Down below them is the Mt Cook Salmon Farm.

title: Oliver's Twist
desc: Jamie prepares some pineapple curry, chutney, and onion bhajis for his band mates.

title: The Chefs' Line
desc: Celebrate the fun of Mexican cuisine as Maeve O'Meara takes us inside the kitchen of el Publico. Maeve and the chefs' line reminisce about the week and delve into delicious new dishes. There's more to Mexican than tacos, including a dish that uses Australian green ants - the tuna tostada. Delight in carnitas de lechon (or suckling pig) and a super vanilla flan.

title: Kriol Kitchen
desc: Denise, Mitch and Ali turn the humble bush turkey into a delicious stew using basic vegetables and Asian sauces.

title: Destination Flavour Down Under
desc: Adam takes a scenic route to Gore and Invercargill on New Zealand's South Island, before heading to the stunning Lake Wakatipu. He spends a long day in the water fishing for trout with a former lawyer, meets a brewer who specialises in craft ciders and beers, and visits a local hunter for some fresh meats. Along the way he collects ingredients for a delicious New Zealand hunter's pie, the perfect dish to consume in front of a fire with snow-dusted mountains as the backdrop.

title: Carnival Eats
desc: Host Noah Cappe knows 'Dela-where' to find amazing fresh seafood, the Delaware State Fair in Harrington. Noah starts with the shrimp dog, succulent shrimp in a corn dog batter, and feels some soul with the Crabtastic Po' Boy, a whole, deep-fried soft shell crab in a sandwich. Noah will also sample a local Delaware classic with the apple scrapple burger before feeding his sweet tooth with the beer battered, deep-fried key lime pie.

desc: Paul has learnt how to be a dairy farmer the hard way. It's time for Paul to make another tough lesson. How will he cope saying goodbye to another farm favourite?

title: Secret Meat Business
desc: A meal fit for a king. Adrian shows us how to make a succulent crown roast lamb sure to have the whole family standing at attention.

title: Secret Meat Business
desc: Adrian dishes up a succulent roast duck cooked in classic Tunisian spices, served on a bed of nutty rice. It's a feast to share with friends and family, or in Adrian's case, enjoy all by yourself.

title: The Cook and the Chef
desc: Maggie gets her hand on the first of the new season's asparagus to make aparagus with soft boiled egg. She proves you don't need fancy implements to prepare asparagus and continues the theme of simplicity with the perfect soft boiled egg.

title: The Cook and the Chef
desc: Longer days and a more generous serving of sun; spring has arrived, and it's the perfect time to get into fresh vegies. Maggie and Simon love spring vegies and they demonstrate that you can have a delicious and filling meal without meat.

title: The Cook and the Chef
desc: Maggie and Simon set out to prove that some frozen produce not only has its merits but in some cases, has its advantages. It's a seafood fiesta with Simon's fish won tons and garlic prawns with rice pilaf, along with Maggie's crispy skin salmon and pea salsa - all frozen, of course. And take out that packet of frozen peas, as Maggie shows us how to make a wonderful frozen pea soup.

title: Freddie Fries Down Under
desc: Freddie and Rob continue their Australian adventure. They get up close and personal with some of the country's deadliest animals by becoming snake catchers for the day, but Rob struggles to overcome his reptile phobia. Travelling to the Gold Coast they catch up with Australia's former strongest man, but things turn surreal when they get embroiled in a car-flipping contest. And their mission to take the Aussie on at their own barbecue game stalls - because of their broken-down van.

title: Lyndey and Blair's Taste of Greece
desc: In the final episode, Lyndey times Blair as he runs the length of the original ancient stadium of Olympia. Next, the pair taste wine from Refosco grapes at Mercouri Winery, and then cook lamb with traditional trachanas. More cooking and eating is followed at Aldemar Restaurant, where they are treated to peppers stuffed with feta and graviera.

title: Lyndey and Blair's Taste of Greece
desc: Lyndey goes back to the kitchen to demonstrate some of the food highlights from her travels through Greece. She shows us how the home cook can share a little of Greece with their own families.

title: Cheese Slices
desc: Roquefort is the most significant of all blue cheeses, it's one of the world's oldest cheeses and one of the few blue cheeses still made from raw milk. To find out what's changed since his last visit to the famous village of Roquefort-sur-Soulzon, Will and Ellie catch up with the makers of Papillon Roquefort, one of the most respected and well-known export brands from the region. Another of the finest boutique Roquefort producers is Carles, and Will takes Ellie into the company's iconic limestone caves to speak to Delphine Carles and sample some of her delectable blue cheeses.

title: Cheese Slices
desc: Under the spotlight in this episode is gorgonzola, the grandaddy of all European blue cheeses made from cow's milk, and its cousin cave-ripened taleggio, which until recently was one of Italy's great soft cheese secrets. Cheese authority Will Studd travels to Northern Italy to see how and where these fascinating cheeses are created. He visits Lombardy, and the maze of underground cellars in the town of Novara where more than 70 percent of gorgonzola is matured. Then it's off to the foothills of the Alps, where caves cooled by melting snow are still used to ripen taleggio the old-fashioned way by the Mauri family.

title: Kylie Kwong: Heart and Soul
desc: Kylie goes straight to the top in Hong Kong, for some of the finest dining in the world.

title: Kylie Kwong: Heart and Soul
desc: Kylie finds trendy shops and bars as well as traditional street food when she explores modern Shanghai.

title: Two Greedy Italians
desc: Chefs Antonio Carluccio and Gennaro Contaldo tour Campania, where they learn how poverty in the area created Italy's best-loved dishes and made the region rich. The duo visit Gennaro's home town Minori to get a lesson in pasta-making from his great aunt, then head to Naples, where they discover the humble beginnings of pizza, and conclude their journey on the Amalfi Coast, an area that gave birth to a new style of food.

title: Destination Flavour Scandinavia
desc: In Stockholm, Sweden, Adam is inside the daring kitchen of Chef Niklas Ekstedt's Michelin restaurant of his namesake, Ekstedt. Niklas shows Adam his rustic pre-electricity style of cooking using only fire, wood, and hay to cook his fine dining dishes. Adam meets Chef and Restaurateur Mathias Pilblad who's opened the only Swedish meatball restaurant in Sweden, and cooks up a classic Swedish meatball dish.

title: Comfort Eating
desc: Nick travels to Leeds with his best mate David Trent, where they tuck into Yorkshire pudding wraps for breakfast before Nick seeks out some chicken soup to help mend his broken heart at Jewish deli, Ira B's. After picking up David's shiny shoes from his parents' house where they share cheesecake, Nick ends his day by fulfilling his dream of meeting his food hero, chef Michael O'Hare, before eating a 16-course taster menu at his restaurant The Man Behind The Curtain.

title: Adolf and Eva: Love and War
desc: From teenage infatuation to her wedding to Hitler and suicide in the fuhrerbunker - this documentary reveals the shocking lengths to which Nazi Germany's secret First Lady went to rise to, and cling to, power. The Nazis kept Eva Braun's affair with Hitler hidden until the very end. But the Fuhrer's inner circle knew she had survived against the odds to become the most powerful woman in Germany. Revealing the truth behind the influential, ambitious and manipulative Nazi bride, this is the story of Eva's incredible rise - and dramatic fall.

title: Last Days Of Solitary
desc: The US is the world leader in solitary confinement, with more than 80,000 American prisoners being held in isolation. In recent years, more than 30 states have begun to experiment with reforms aimed at reducing the use of solitary. Filmed over three years, this searing documentary offers the most comprehensive exploration of this controversial practice, with immersive, unprecedented access to the solitary unit at Maine State Prison. It portrays the psychological integration of human beings, and the challenge of how to deal with men considered the most dangerous and difficult in the state.

title: Loving Pablo
desc: The extraordinary story of the volatile love affair between Colombia's most famous journalist, Virginia Vallejo, and the world's most feared drug lord, Pablo Escobar. When Virginia first met Pablo, she was drawn to him by his charisma and contagious passion for his country and the people he loves. As their passionate affair intensified, so did the brutal violence and tyranny that surrounded Escobar's empire. As her world comes crashing down around her, Virginia must decide if she will support the man she loves or help bring down one of the most vicious criminals the world has ever known in this amazing story inspired by true events from Virginia's best-selling memoir.

title: Their Finest
desc: A British film crew attempt to boost morale during World War II by making a propaganda film after the Blitzkrieg.

title: The Grand Budapest Hotel
desc: Recounts the adventures of Gustave H, a legendary concierge at a famous European hotel between the wars, and Zero Moustafa, the lobby boy who becomes his most trusted friend.

title: Romeo and Juliet
desc: Romeo and Juliet secretly wed despite the sworn contempt their families hold for each other. It is not long, however, before a chain of fateful events changes the lives of both families forever.

title: The Secret of Moonacre
desc: This is an enchanting tale of magic and adventure. It follows the quest of 13-year-old orphan Maria Merryweather, who is sent away to live with her uncle, Sir Benjamin, in the mysterious Moonacre Manor. It is there that Maria uncovers the dark truth of the ancient curse that has nourished the feud that has been destroying Moonacre Valley for centuries. She has only until the next full moon to undo the curse and save Moonacre from destruction.

title: City of Ember
desc: An underground city is supposed to give shelter for 200 years. Unfortunately, power supply is failing, slowly but surely.

title: Our Little Sister
desc: Three sisters, Sachi, Yoshino and Chika, live together in a large house in the seaside city of Kamakura. When their father, absent from the family home for the last 15 years, dies, they travel to the countryside for his funeral and meet their shy 14-year-old half-sister, Suzu. Bonding quickly with the orphaned Suzu, they invite her to live with them. Suzu eagerly agrees, and a new life of joyful discovery begins for the four siblings.

title: White Tuft, the Little Beaver
desc: A beaver couple live by their dam. As the seasons go by, they have babies, gather food, maintain their dam, play and swim, and, of course, defend their territory against predators and intruders. After one of their young gets lost in the forest, the mother and father beaver search frantically for him, while he is rescued by an unlikely ally.

title: Romeo and Juliet
desc: Romeo and Juliet secretly wed despite the sworn contempt their families hold for each other. It is not long, however, before a chain of fateful events changes the lives of both families forever.

title: Boychoir
desc: A troubled 11-year-old boy at a prestigious east coast music school clashes with the school's demanding choir master, in this inspiring drama the entire family can enjoy. The story of a talented youngster struggling against the odds to find his voice.

title: Summer Wars
desc: Kenji Koiso, an 11th grade math genius, solves a complex equation and inadvertently puts a virtual world's artificial intelligence in a position to destroy the Earth.

title: Tell No One
desc: Eight years ago, Doctor Alex Beck's wife Margot was brutally murdered and a serial killer was charged with her death. But the discovery of two bodies on the shores of the lake where Margot was killed forces the police to reopen the case, with new evidence casting suspicion on Alex. At the same time, Dr Beck is receiving strange email messages - from his presumably dead wife.

title: Angel-A
desc: Andre, a kind-hearted small-time crook, owes a large sum of money to one of Paris' most ruthless gangsters. Unable to pay by the deadline, he is about to end it all when he is visited by an angel.

title: Freddie Fries Down Under
desc: Freddie and Rob continue their Australian adventure. They get up close and personal with some of the country's deadliest animals by becoming snake catchers for the day, but Rob struggles to overcome his reptile phobia. Travelling to the Gold Coast they catch up with Australia's former strongest man, but things turn surreal when they get embroiled in a car-flipping contest. And their mission to take the Aussie on at their own barbecue game stalls - because of their broken-down van.

title: Lyndey and Blair's Taste of Greece
desc: In the final episode, Lyndey times Blair as he runs the length of the original ancient stadium of Olympia. Next, the pair taste wine from Refosco grapes at Mercouri Winery, and then cook lamb with traditional trachanas. More cooking and eating is followed at Aldemar Restaurant, where they are treated to peppers stuffed with feta and graviera.

title: Lyndey and Blair's Taste of Greece
desc: Lyndey goes back to the kitchen to demonstrate some of the food highlights from her travels through Greece. She shows us how the home cook can share a little of Greece with their own families.

title: Cheese Slices
desc: Roquefort is the most significant of all blue cheeses, it's one of the world's oldest cheeses and one of the few blue cheeses still made from raw milk. To find out what's changed since his last visit to the famous village of Roquefort-sur-Soulzon, Will and Ellie catch up with the makers of Papillon Roquefort, one of the most respected and well-known export brands from the region. Another of the finest boutique Roquefort producers is Carles, and Will takes Ellie into the company's iconic limestone caves to speak to Delphine Carles and sample some of her delectable blue cheeses.

title: Cheese Slices
desc: Under the spotlight in this episode is gorgonzola, the grandaddy of all European blue cheeses made from cow's milk, and its cousin cave-ripened taleggio, which until recently was one of Italy's great soft cheese secrets. Cheese authority Will Studd travels to Northern Italy to see how and where these fascinating cheeses are created. He visits Lombardy, and the maze of underground cellars in the town of Novara where more than 70 percent of gorgonzola is matured. Then it's off to the foothills of the Alps, where caves cooled by melting snow are still used to ripen taleggio the old-fashioned way by the Mauri family.

title: Kylie Kwong: Heart and Soul
desc: Kylie goes straight to the top in Hong Kong, for some of the finest dining in the world.

title: Kylie Kwong: Heart and Soul
desc: Kylie finds trendy shops and bars as well as traditional street food when she explores modern Shanghai.

title: Two Greedy Italians
desc: Chefs Antonio Carluccio and Gennaro Contaldo tour Campania, where they learn how poverty in the area created Italy's best-loved dishes and made the region rich. The duo visit Gennaro's home town Minori to get a lesson in pasta-making from his great aunt, then head to Naples, where they discover the humble beginnings of pizza, and conclude their journey on the Amalfi Coast, an area that gave birth to a new style of food.

title: Destination Flavour Scandinavia
desc: In Stockholm, Sweden, Adam is inside the daring kitchen of Chef Niklas Ekstedt's Michelin restaurant of his namesake, Ekstedt. Niklas shows Adam his rustic pre-electricity style of cooking using only fire, wood, and hay to cook his fine dining dishes. Adam meets Chef and Restaurateur Mathias Pilblad who's opened the only Swedish meatball restaurant in Sweden, and cooks up a classic Swedish meatball dish.

desc: Double trouble. Adrian combines two of his favourite proteins in an indulgent Canadian dish: bacon-wrapped duck breast tournedos.

title: The Cook and the Chef
desc: Chefs love working with colour and contrast, but Maggie and Simon love a challenge so this week they're going blonde. White asparagus, light coloured meats, garlic, white chocolate, coconut and meringue all make the 'blonde food' menu, and with the use of simple sauces and balancing of flavours the cook and the chef prove that blonde doesn't mean bland. It's a program packed with blonde tips and worth watching just to see how the theme goes to Simon's head.

title: The Cook and the Chef
desc: When offal is mentioned, most of us think of the internal organs of animals, but the word also refers to anything that is considered worthless or thrown away. This episode, Maggie and Simon demonstrate that some ingredients which are considered 'junk food' can be tasty if they're prepared with love and attention.

title: The Cook and the Chef
desc: It's the middle of spring and the sunshine and longer days are a great excuse for people to get together and enjoy good company and good food. In this program, Maggie and Simon whip up dishes that'll not only impress the crowd but are easy to transport to any get-together. Maggie's 'moveable feast' is a creamy asparagus and leek tart, a whole meal encased in a sour cream pastry and ready to go. Simon shows us how to make a beautifully textured goat cheese lasagne that can be transported using a gourmet 'must-have', the cardboard box.

title: Donal's Kitchen Hero Feast
desc: With Christmas fast approaching, Donal visits a turkey farm and a bakery selling mince pies. The garden florists in the Powerscourt Centre will be showing Donal how to decorate a table at Christmas.

title: Jimmy Shu's Taste of the Territory
desc: Jimmy tastes some of Darwin's most popular street food from the stalls of the Parap Saturday market. Jimmy talks about Darwin's laksa obsession, and visits Mary's Laksa - a stall who have been serving laska for over 20 yeas.

title: Diana's Asia Unplated
desc: Southern Indian cooking is distinctly influenced by the abundance of fresh fruit and vegetables found in the region. Sarah Todd's love of Indian cuisine has led her to open up restaurants in Goa and Mumbai, documented on the television series, My Restaurant in India. Sarah starts with vindaloo pork ribs topped with Goan bhel, before cooking a vegetarian dish of baked cauliflower with pineapple sansav. Diana finishes the theme with a traditional dessert called sweet appam, filled with carmelised banana, the perfect snack on a balmy afternoon.

title: Bonacini's Italy
desc: Simplicity is key with Sicilian cuisine and Michael explores just how the region balances simplicity with intensity through four flavourful dishes. He starts with an antipasto of folded flatbread with ricotta and fennel seeds, and a primo of broccoli and sausage rigatoni.

title: Rick Stein's Far Eastern Odyssey
desc: One of Britain's most revered chefs and successful authors, Rick Stein sets off on an epic culinary journey to explore the far east's most diverse food cultures, which have soared to the heights of popularity the world over. Rick begins his odyssey in Cambodia, a country still recovering from the regime of the Khmer Rouge. Rick discovers the joys of freshly caught swimmer crabs cooked with green peppercorns from Kampot, once the king of pepper. He learns how to cook the most famous dish in the country, fish amok, made with lemongrass and coconut. He also samples lok lak, an extremely popular and delicious dish made with stir-fried strips of marinated beef.

title: Jonathan Phang's Gourmet Express
desc: Starting in Australia's thriving cosmopolitan west coast city of Perth, Jonathan lives like a true Aussie when he cooks prawns on the barbie with chef Russell Blaikie, gets a little pick-me-up when he samples an espresso martini, and pays homage to the area's printing press history with chef Shane Watson's black and white menu.

title: The Sweet Life With Elise Strachan
desc: Elise is joined in the kitchen by My Kitchen Rules 2016 winners Tasia and Gracia Seger, who put a unique Indonesian spin on the French classic: brulee. Yasoda Welsh makes Indian-inspired hand-painted mandala cheesecakes.

title: Destination Flavour Scandinavia

Adam takes in a new Swedish project called Hoffice, which turns apartments into temporary co-working spaces, and Adam makes delicious semlor in the home-office kitchen.

title: ABC News Hour
desc: Know the latest on the rapidly changing COVID-19 situation as Australia eases restrictions and reopens the nation. Gemma Veness brings you up-to-date information and breaking news as the social and economic recovery begins.

title: ABC Evening News
desc: All the news you need to stay up-to-date on the coronavirus pandemic. Andrew Geoghegan brings you the latest on the global response, and updated information on the easing of restrictions as we navigate the road to recovery.

title: ABC National News
desc: Australia is adapting to some kind of normality as restrictions are eased and we return to life, work, school, public transport and shopping with social distancing. Andrew Geoghegan brings you the latest news.

title: ABC News Tonight
desc: The coronavirus pandemic has changed the way we live, work, learn, socialise and shop. With the number of new cases falling, Australia is now on the long road to recovery. Andrew Geoghegan brings you the latest developments.

title: The Business
desc: Elysse Morgan presents Australia's leading daily business and finance show, bringing you up to date on market moves, economic trends and the forces affecting business big and small.

title: ABC News Update
desc: The latest headlines updating you on the day's top stories from across Australia and around the world.

title: The Drum
desc: When we're suddenly disconnected, we need to stay in touch more than ever. To know the facts and discuss the details, get your daily dose of the program with Ellen Fanning and our panel of informed contributors and guests.

title: The World
desc: Your nightly snapshot of what's going on in the world. Beverley O'Connor brings you the latest news on the global response to the coronavirus pandemic, and speaks with experts, reporters, and people affected by the crisis.

title: ABC Nightly News
desc: Everything you need to know about the rapidly changing COVID-19 situation, including the healthcare emergency, economic crisis and the impact on jobs, schools, aged care, plus social dislocation, travel restrictions and more.

Know the latest on coronavirus, how it affects you, your family, community, jobs and school. Find out what you can do to stop the spread and protect your loved ones, healthcare workers, the young, old and our most vulnerable.

title: Tin Star
desc: British detective and recovering alcoholic Jim Worth is adjusting to the quiet life in the Canadian Rockies after moving from London to the mountain idyll of Little Big Bear with his family.

title: Tin Star
desc: The Worth family are left devastated by the tragedy that has taken place. Racked by guilt at escaping the bullet meant for him, Jim begins a slow, inexorable slide back to the comfort of a whiskey bottle. Fearing the house is no longer safe, he secures Anna in a hotel, and attempts to bury his grief in work by picking the North Stream murder case back up, instinctively believing there is some connection to his own loss.

title: North to South: The Full Journey
desc: A spectacular overland route from Auckland on New Zealand's north island, down to the south by way of multiple forms of transport including railways, sailing and driving. The city gives way to rolling pastures, volcanic extremes, tranquil waterways, the rough Otago high country and grandeur of the Southern Alps and Milford Sound.

title: The Attack - Countdown To Terror
desc: A tense cat-and-mouse narrative about a jihadi sleeper cell planning a massacre at an iconic British event. Faced with this scenario, real counterterrorism experts reveal the tactics being used to try and foil such plots, showing how elite decision-makers in the police, the government and the security services work together to prevent a terrorist outrage. All the while they have to balance the impact of their decisions on civil liberties and public safety, while grappling with the complex legal and moral questions surrounding counterterrorism.
